Azure Tags are key-value pairs used to organize and categorize resources for management, billing, and automation.

Common tag examples:

* Environment: Dev/Test/Prod
* Owner: Team name
* CostCenter: Department

For example, tagging all production resources with “Environment=Prod” helps in filtering and managing them easily.

A real-life use case is cost tracking. Organizations can generate cost reports based on tags to understand spending per department.

Another example is automation, where scripts can identify and act on resources based on tags.

Tags improve visibility, organization, and cost management.
